BY MAYOWA SAMUEL The decomposed bodies of the two abducted wives and five children of the Chief of Mutumbiyu Justices Chiefdom in Taraba State, Justice Sani Muhammed (rtd), have been found. According to the monarch, the decomposed bodies were found in the early hours of Saturday and would be buried at Mutumbiyu. He stated that, “The bodies of the members of my family killed by the kidnappers were found and will be brought to Mutumbiyu for burial.” The monarch had two weeks disclosed that eight of his family members were kidnapped by unknown gunmen suspected to be kidnappers at his residence in Jalingo. The monarch explained that among the eight kidnapped, a 14-year-old boy escaped from the kidnappers two days ago and was taken to the palace.